{"name":"task","description":"Generic table for tasks that need to be performed, used as a parent table for many other task-based tables like incidents and changes.","summary":"ServiceNow is a cloud-based platform designed to help organizations manage digital workflows for enterprise operations. The object \"task\" in ServiceNow generally refers to a record in the system that represents work to be done. Tasks can be related to incidents, changes, problems, and other work items within the ServiceNow platform.\n\nHere's a summary of the object \"task\" in ServiceNow:\n\n1. **Definition**: A \"task\" in ServiceNow is a record that represents any work item that needs to be tracked and managed. Tasks can include incidents, service requests, change requests, problems, and more.\n\n2. **Attributes**: Tasks have several attributes, including:\n   - **Task Number**: A unique identifier for the task.\n   - **Short Description**: A brief summary of the task.\n   - **Description**: A detailed explanation of the task.\n   - **Priority**: Indicates the urgency and impact of the task.\n   - **State**: Represents the current status of the task (e.g., New, In Progress, Resolved, Closed).\n   - **Assignment Group**: The group responsible for completing the task.\n   - **Assigned To**: The individual responsible for completing the task.\n   - **Created Date**: The date and time the task was created.\n   - **Due Date**: The date by which the task should be completed.\n\n3. **Lifecycle**: Tasks go through various states from creation to completion. Common states include New, In Progress, On Hold, Resolved, and Closed.\n\n4. **Relationships**: Tasks can be related to other records in the system, such as:\n   - **Incidents**: A task may be created to resolve an incident.\n   - **Changes**: A task may be part of a change request process.\n   - **Problems**: A task may be related to addressing the root cause of a problem.\n\n5. **Automation**: ServiceNow provides automation features, such as workflows and business rules, to manage tasks efficiently. These automations can assign tasks, send notifications, and update task statuses based on predefined conditions.\n\n6. **Reporting and Tracking**: ServiceNow offers robust reporting and tracking capabilities to monitor task progress, performance metrics, and SLA (Service Level Agreement) adherence.\n\n7. **Customization**: Tasks can be customized to fit the specific needs of an organization, including custom fields, forms, and workflows.\n\nOverall, the \"task\" object in ServiceNow is a fundamental component used to manage and track various types of","attributes":[{"name":"parent","type":"reference"},{"name":"made_sla","type":"boolean"},{"name":"watch_list","type":"glide_list"},{"name":"upon_reject","type":"string"},{"name":"sys_updated_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"task_effective_number","type":"string"},{"name":"approval_history","type":"journal"},{"name":"skills","type":"glide_list"},{"name":"number","type":"string"},{"name":"sys_updated_by","type":"string"},{"name":"opened_by","type":"reference"},{"name":"user_input","type":"user_input"},{"name":"sys_created_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"sys_domain","type":"domain_id"},{"name":"state","type":"integer"},{"name":"sys_created_by","type":"string"},{"name":"route_reason","type":"integer"},{"name":"knowledge","type":"boolean"},{"name":"order","type":"integer"},{"name":"closed_at","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"cmdb_ci","type":"reference"},{"name":"delivery_plan","type":"reference"},{"name":"impact","type":"integer"},{"name":"contract","type":"reference"},{"name":"active","type":"boolean"},{"name":"work_notes_list","type":"glide_list"},{"name":"business_service","type":"reference"},{"name":"priority","type":"integer"},{"name":"sys_domain_path","type":"domain_path"},{"name":"time_worked","type":"timer"},{"name":"expected_start","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"opened_at","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"business_duration","type":"gli